headline: Lennar Earnings Got a Boost From Opendoor. Why The Stock is Falling Anyway.
summary: Anyone looking for signs that the worst is over for the housing industry didn’t get them in Lennar’s earnings, released Thursday night. Lennar earned $2.29 a share in its third quarter on $8.8 billion in revenue.
